
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `gcov-dump` baraye biron keshidan etela'at az file-haye data coverage ke az `gcov` gerefte shode, estefade mishe. In dastoor be shoma komak mikone ta bebinid kodum khat-ha az code-e shoma ejra shode va chand bar ejra shode.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `gcov-dump -l`  --> 📜 Namayesh khatt be khatt (line-by-line) etela'at az file-e coverage.
    🔹 `gcov-dump -s`  --> 📊 Namayesh ye kholase az etela'at coverage.
    🔹 `gcov-dump -v`  --> 🔊 Namayesh etela'at bishtar dar morede amal kard-e `gcov-dump`.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ gcov-dump myprogram.gcda

    🔹 Biron keshidan etela'at az file `myprogram.gcda` va chap kardan an be stdout.

    $ gcov-dump -l myprogram.gcda

    🔹 Biron keshidan etela'at khatt be khatt az file `myprogram.gcda` va chap kardan an be stdout.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ gcov-dump -s myprogram.gcda

    🔹 Namayesh ye kholase az file coverage `myprogram.gcda`, shamel darsad khat-haye ejra shode.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `gcov-dump` command is used to extract data coverage information from coverage data files generated by `gcov`.  It helps you see which lines of your code were executed and how many times.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `gcov-dump -l`  --> 📜 Display line-by-line coverage information from the coverage file.
    🔹 `gcov-dump -s`  --> 📊 Display a summary of the coverage information.
    🔹 `gcov-dump -v`  --> 🔊 Increase verbosity, providing more detailed output about `gcov-dump`'s operation.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ gcov-dump myprogram.gcda

    🔹 Extract data from the `myprogram.gcda` file and print it to stdout.

    $ gcov-dump -l myprogram.gcda

    🔹 Extract line-by-line information from the `myprogram.gcda` file and print it to stdout.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ gcov-dump -s myprogram.gcda

    🔹 Display a summary of the coverage file `myprogram.gcda`, including the percentage of lines executed.
